Dialogue: 2,0:01:18.30,0:01:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Do you remember the storm?
Dialogue: 2,0:01:21.97,0:01:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}The bronze doors banging.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:24.57,0:01:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}The roses in cellophane.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:28.76,0:01:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}The man who threw the get together party
Dialogue: 2,0:01:31.21,0:01:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and was never seen again.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:33.16,0:01:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Do you remember how the sun came out on our last evening
Dialogue: 2,0:01:37.42,0:01:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}just as it has done today?
Dialogue: 2,0:01:44.58,0:01:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}So much to remember.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:49.69,0:01:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}How many days have there been since then
Dialogue: 2,0:01:51.58,0:01:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}when we haven't seen each other
Dialogue: 2,0:01:54.99,0:01:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}A hundred.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:56.30,0:01:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Not so many.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:57.94,0:01:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Two Christmases
Dialogue: 2,0:02:00.66,0:02:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}to keep up appearances for the sake of the children.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:08.73,0:02:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}And the three days of good taste
Dialogue: 2,0:02:10.76,0:02:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}before I followed you to Capri.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:12.75,0:02:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Our first summer.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:17.37,0:02:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Do you remember how I hung about in Naples and then followed.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:21.49,0:02:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}How we met by arrangement on the hill path
Dialogue: 2,0:02:24.48,0:02:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and how flat it felt.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:26.06,0:02:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I went back to the villa and said Papa
Dialogue: 2,0:02:27.82,0:02:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Who do you think has arrived at the hotel?
Dialogue: 2,0:02:29.78,0:02:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}And he said Charles Ryder, I suppose.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:31.75,0:02:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}And I said Whatever made you think of him?
Dialogue: 2,0:02:33.69,0:02:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}And he said He seems to have a penchant for my children.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:40.26,0:02:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}There was a time when you had jaundice and wouldn't let me see you.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:43.44,0:02:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}And when I had flu you were afraid to come.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:49.16,0:02:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}A hundred days.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:51.00,0:02:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Out of two years and a bit.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:55.73,0:02:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Not a day's coldness or mistrust or disappointment.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:00.07,0:03:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Never that.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:08.29,0:03:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Let's go and change.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:19.93,0:03:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}How many more do you think?
Dialogue: 2,0:03:23.84,0:03:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Another hundred?
Dialogue: 2,0:03:25.05,0:03:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}A lifetime.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:27.96,0:03:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I want to marry you, Charles.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:30.87,0:03:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}One day, why now?
Dialogue: 2,0:03:33.00,0:03:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}War, this year, next year, sometime soon.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:37.44,0:03:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I want a year or two with you of real peace.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:42.64,0:03:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Isn't this peace?
Dialogue: 2,0:03:51.77,0:03:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}What do you mean by peace if not this?
Dialogue: 2,0:03:54.44,0:03:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}So much more.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:56.11,0:03:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Marriage isn't a thing we can take
Dialogue: 2,0:03:59.61,0:04:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}when the mood strikes us. There must be a divorce
Dialogue: 2,0:04:01.90,0:04:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}two divorces.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:03.90,0:04:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}We must make plans.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:07.40,0:04:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Plans, divorce, war
Dialogue: 2,0:04:11.39,0:04:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}On an evening like this.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:15.11,0:04:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Sometimes I feel the past and the future pressing so hard
Dialogue: 2,0:04:18.33,0:04:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}on either side there doesn't seem room for the present at all.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:22.18,0:04:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Yes, Wilcox?
Dialogue: 2,0:04:23.24,0:04:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Lord Brideshead's just telephoned, my Lady.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:25.59,0:04:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He says not to wait dinner for him please
Dialogue: 2,0:04:27.77,0:04:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}as he'll be a little late. Thank you, Wilcox.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:33.78,0:04:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It seem months since he was last here.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:37.15,0:04:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Yes
Dialogue: 2,0:04:38.00,0:04:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}What does he do in London?
Dialogue: 2,0:04:40.29,0:04:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It was often a matter for speculation between us
Dialogue: 2,0:04:42.69,0:04:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Giving birth to many fantasies
Dialogue: 2,0:04:44.83,0:04:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}for Bridey was a mystery.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:46.93,0:04:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}The talk
Dialogue: 2,0:04:48.38,0:04:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}of his going into the army
Dialogue: 2,0:04:50.51,0:04:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and into parliament and into a monastery
Dialogue: 2,0:04:52.80,0:04:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}had all come to nothing.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:53.86,0:04:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}All that he was known with certainty to have done
Dialogue: 2,0:04:57.60,0:05:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and this because in a season of scant news
Dialogue: 2,0:05:00.48,0:05:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}it had formed the subject of a newspaper article
Dialogue: 2,0:05:02.73,0:05:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}entitled "Peer's Unusual Hobby"
Dialogue: 2,0:05:05.76,0:05:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}was to form a collection of match boxes.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:15.50,0:05:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Hello Bridey.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:16.37,0:05:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Oh Bridey, we're almost finished.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:18.49,0:05:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Well, well, only you two.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:20.66,0:05:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I hoped to find Rex here.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:24.20,0:05:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}How are you?
Dialogue: 2,0:05:25.67,0:05:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}What's the news?
Dialogue: 2,0:05:27.08,0:05:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}As a matter of fact I do have some news
Dialogue: 2,0:05:29.65,0:05:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}but it can wait.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:31.23,0:05:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Tell us now.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:36.63,0:05:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}How's the painting Charles?
Dialogue: 2,0:05:38.07,0:05:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Which painting?
Dialogue: 2,0:05:39.49,0:05:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Whatever you have on the stocks.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:41.87,0:05:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Well, I've begun a picture of Julia
Dialogue: 2,0:05:44.18,0:05:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}but the light was difficult all day today.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:47.16,0:05:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Julia?
Dialogue: 2,0:05:48.03,0:05:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Haven't you done her before?
Dialogue: 2,0:05:49.64,0:05:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I suppose it's a change from architecture and much more difficult.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:52.81,0:05:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}The world is full of different subjects.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:55.20,0:05:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Very true, Bridey.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:58.51,0:05:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}If I were a painter
Dialogue: 2,0:05:59.57,0:06:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I should choose a different subject every time.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:02.85,0:06:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Really?
Dialogue: 2,0:06:04.09,0:06:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}What sort of subjects?
Dialogue: 2,0:06:06.27,0:06:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Oh I don't know really
Dialogue: 2,0:06:08.38,0:06:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}subjects with plenty of action in them like
Dialogue: 2,0:06:11.54,0:06:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Macbeth, perhaps.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:22.19,0:06:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}By the way, I've been meaning to ask you
Dialogue: 2,0:06:23.67,0:06:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}What happened to mother's jewels?
Dialogue: 2,0:06:25.10,0:06:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Cordelia and I had most of her things.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:27.82,0:06:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}This was hers.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:29.09,0:06:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}And this.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:30.87,0:06:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}The rest went to the bank.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:33.73,0:06:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Aren't there some rather famous rubies
Dialogue: 2,0:06:35.57,0:06:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}someone was telling me?
Dialogue: 2,0:06:36.38,0:06:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Yes, a necklace. Mummy often used to wear it
Dialogue: 2,0:06:38.76,0:06:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}don't you remember?
Dialogue: 2,0:06:40.59,0:06:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Why, anyway?
Dialogue: 2,0:06:41.86,0:06:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I just thought I'd like to take a look at them some day.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:50.31,0:06:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I say Papa isn't going to pop them, is he?
Dialogue: 2,0:06:52.69,0:06:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He's not in debt again?
Dialogue: 2,0:06:54.33,0:06:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}No, no nothing like that.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:59.95,0:07:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Come on Bridey, don't be so mysterious. Out with it.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:15.72,0:07:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Well, you have only to wait until Monday
Dialogue: 2,0:07:17.59,0:07:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}to see it in black and white in the newspapers.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:20.50,0:07:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I am engaged to be married.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:22.14,0:07:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I hope you're pleased.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:23.49,0:07:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Bridey! How very exciting!
Dialogue: 2,0:07:25.59,0:07:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Who to?
Dialogue: 2,0:07:27.46,0:07:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Oh, no one you know. Is she pretty?
Dialogue: 2,0:07:29.75,0:07:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I don't think you would exactly call her pretty.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:32.88,0:07:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Comely is the word I think of in her connection.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:36.57,0:07:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}She's a big woman.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:38.62,0:07:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Fat?
Dialogue: 2,0:07:40.17,0:07:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}No, big.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:41.66,0:07:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}She's called Mrs. Muspratt.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:44.06,0:07:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Her Christian name is Beryl.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:46.39,0:07:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I've known her for quite a long time
Dialogue: 2,0:07:48.61,0:07:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}But until last year she had a husband
Dialogue: 2,0:07:50.78,0:07:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}now she's a widow.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:52.50,0:07:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Why do you laugh?
Dialogue: 2,0:07:55.59,0:07:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I'm sorry. It's not in the least funny.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:57.39,0:07:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It's just so unexpected.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:01.87,0:08:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Is she
Dialogue: 2,0:08:04.82,0:08:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Is she about your own age?
Dialogue: 2,0:08:06.75,0:08:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Just about, I believe.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:08.69,0:08:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}She has three children
Dialogue: 2,0:08:10.34,0:08:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}the eldest boy has just gone to Ampleforth.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:12.96,0:08:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}She is not at all well off.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:14.65,0:08:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Where did you find her?
Dialogue: 2,0:08:16.27,0:08:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Her late husband, Admiral Muspratt
Dialogue: 2,0:08:20.65,0:08:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}collected matchboxes.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:26.83,0:08:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You're not marrying her for her matchboxes?
Dialogue: 2,0:08:29.51,0:08:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}No, the whole collection went to the Falmouth Town Library.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:32.30,0:08:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I have great affection for her.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:34.59,0:08:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}In spite of all her difficulties
Dialogue: 2,0:08:36.85,0:08:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}she's a very cheerful woman
Dialogue: 2,0:08:38.92,0:08:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}very fond of acting.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:40.83,0:08:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}She is a member of the Catholic Player's Guild.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:45.48,0:08:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Does Papa know?
Dialogue: 2,0:08:46.56,0:08:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I had a letter from him this morning giving me his approval.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:49.34,0:08:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He's been urging me for some time to marry.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:51.69,0:08:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Well
Dialogue: 2,0:08:56.07,0:08:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Congratulations, Bridey.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:58.03,0:08:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Yes.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:00.16,0:09:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Congratulations.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:01.37,0:09:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Thank you. Thank you.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:03.79,0:09:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I think I'm very fortunate.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:27.41,0:09:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Bridey, when are we going to meet her?
Dialogue: 2,0:09:28.68,0:09:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I do think you might have brought her down with you.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:32.96,0:09:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Bridey
Dialogue: 2,0:09:34.06,0:09:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}you sly, smug old brute why didn't you bring her here?
Dialogue: 2,0:09:38.61,0:09:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Oh, I couldn't do that, you know.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:39.95,0:09:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Why couldn't you?
Dialogue: 2,0:09:40.97,0:09:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I'm dying to meet her.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:43.30,0:09:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Let's ring her up and ask her.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:45.69,0:09:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}She'll think us most peculiar
Dialogue: 2,0:09:47.68,0:09:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}leaving her alone at a time like this.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:49.62,0:09:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}She has the children.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:50.65,0:09:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Besides
Dialogue: 2,0:09:52.47,0:09:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}you are peculiar, aren't you?
Dialogue: 2,0:09:54.05,0:09:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}What can you mean?
Dialogue: 2,0:09:56.86,0:09:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I could hardly ask her here, as things are.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:59.43,0:10:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It wouldn't be suitable.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:00.54,0:10:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}After all, I'm only a lodger here.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:02.48,0:10:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}This is Rex's house at the moment, so far as it's anybody's.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:05.63,0:10:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}What goes on here is his business. But I couldn't bring Beryl here.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:10.79,0:10:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I simply don't understand.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:12.98,0:10:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Of course
Dialogue: 2,0:10:16.09,0:10:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Rex and I want her to come.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:17.42,0:10:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Oh yes, I don't doubt that.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:18.68,0:10:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}But the difficulty is quite otherwise.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:21.18,0:10:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You must understand that Beryl is a woman
Dialogue: 2,0:10:23.64,0:10:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Of strict Catholic principles
Dialogue: 2,0:10:25.07,0:10:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}fortified by the prejudices of the middle classes.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:27.84,0:10:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I couldn't possibly bring her here.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:30.11,0:10:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It's a matter of indifference whether you choose to live in sin
Dialogue: 2,0:10:33.63,0:10:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}With Rex or Charles or both
Dialogue: 2,0:10:35.10,0:10:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I have always avoided inquiry into the details of your ménage
Dialogue: 2,0:10:38.30,0:10:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}but, in no case would Beryl consent to be your guest.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:44.51,0:10:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Why you pompous ass?
Dialogue: 2,0:10:49.94,0:10:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I may have given the impression that this
Dialogue: 2,0:10:52.03,0:10:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}was a marriage of convenience.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:53.56,0:10:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I cannot speak for Beryl.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:55.55,0:10:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}No doubt the security of my position
Dialogue: 2,0:10:58.12,0:11:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}has some influence on her.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:01.06,0:11:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Indeed, she has said as much.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:03.07,0:11:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}But for myself, let me emphasis
Dialogue: 2,0:11:05.04,0:11:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I am ardently attracted.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:07.60,0:11:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Bridey
Dialogue: 2,0:11:10.15,0:11:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}what a bloody offensive thing to say to Julia.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:12.27,0:11:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}There was nothing she should object to.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:14.94,0:11:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I was merely stating a fact well known to her.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:48.96,0:12:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Aren't you cold?
Dialogue: 2,0:12:55.85,0:12:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}My darling, what is it?
Dialogue: 2,0:13:01.10,0:13:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Why do you mind?
Dialogue: 2,0:13:02.42,0:13:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}What does it matter what the old booby says?
Dialogue: 2,0:13:06.00,0:13:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I don't.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:09.06,0:13:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It doesn't.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:10.17,0:13:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It's just the shock.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:13.89,0:13:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Don't laugh at me.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:19.75,0:13:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}How dare he speak to you like that?
Dialogue: 2,0:13:23.18,0:13:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}The cold-blooded old humbug
Dialogue: 2,0:13:27.92,0:13:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}No, it's not that.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:29.40,0:13:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He's quite right.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:33.01,0:13:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}They know all about it, Bridey and his widow.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:39.39,0:13:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}They bought it for a penny at the church door.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:43.59,0:13:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You can get anything there for a penny in black and white
Dialogue: 2,0:13:46.31,0:13:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and nobody to see you pay. Just take your tract.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:49.25,0:13:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}There youve got it.
Dialogue: 2,0:13:53.81,0:13:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}All in one word, too
Dialogue: 2,0:13:57.17,0:14:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}one little, flat, deadly word that covers a lifetime.
Dialogue: 2,0:14:01.24,0:14:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Living in sin
Dialogue: 2,0:14:03.59,0:14:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}not just doing wrong, as I did when I went to America
Dialogue: 2,0:14:07.49,0:14:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}doing wrong, knowing it is wrong
Dialogue: 2,0:14:08.83,0:14:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}stopping it, forgetting it.
Dialogue: 2,0:14:11.06,0:14:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}That's not what they mean. That's not Bridey's pennyworth.
Dialogue: 2,0:14:18.09,0:14:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He means just what it says.
Dialogue: 2,0:14:20.85,0:14:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Living in sin, every hour
Dialogue: 2,0:14:23.67,0:14:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}every day, year in year out.
Dialogue: 2,0:14:29.10,0:14:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Always the same.
Dialogue: 2,0:14:32.81,0:14:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Like an idiot child, carefully nursed
Dialogue: 2,0:14:35.09,0:14:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}guarded from the world.
Dialogue: 2,0:14:36.28,0:14:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Poor Julia they say, 'she can't go out. "
Dialogue: 2,0:14:38.66,0:14:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}She's got to take care of her little sin.
Dialogue: 2,0:14:41.01,0:14:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}A pity it ever lived they say
Dialogue: 2,0:14:42.92,0:14:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}But it's so strong
Dialogue: 2,0:14:48.12,0:14:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Children like that always are.
Dialogue: 2,0:14:51.33,0:14:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Julia's so good to her little, mad sin.
Dialogue: 2,0:15:01.71,0:15:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}All those years when I was trying
Dialogue: 2,0:15:06.07,0:15:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}to be a good wife
Dialogue: 2,0:15:08.94,0:15:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}in the cigar smoke.
Dialogue: 2,0:15:14.09,0:15:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}When I was trying
Dialogue: 2,0:15:16.97,0:15:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}To bear his child
Dialogue: 2,0:15:19.79,0:15:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Torn in pieces by something already dead
Dialogue: 2,0:15:29.53,0:15:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}putting him away, forgetting him, finding you
Dialogue: 2,0:15:33.87,0:15:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}the past two years with you
Dialogue: 2,0:15:39.41,0:15:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}All the future with you or without you
Dialogue: 2,0:15:45.27,0:15:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}War coming
Dialogue: 2,0:15:50.04,0:15:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}World ending
Dialogue: 2,0:15:55.84,0:15:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}sin.
Dialogue: 2,0:16:03.70,0:16:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It's a word from so long ago.
Dialogue: 2,0:16:09.36,0:16:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}From Nanny Hawkins stitching by the hearth
Dialogue: 2,0:16:14.18,0:16:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and the nightlight burning before the Sacred Heart.
Dialogue: 2,0:16:21.60,0:16:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Me and Cordelia with the catechism, in Mummy's room
Dialogue: 2,0:16:24.43,0:16:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}before lunch, on Sundays.
Dialogue: 2,0:16:31.31,0:16:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Mummy carrying my sin with her to church.
Dialogue: 2,0:16:34.87,0:16:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Bowed under it.
Dialogue: 2,0:16:40.51,0:16:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Mummy dying with my sin eating at her
Dialogue: 2,0:16:44.92,0:16:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}more cruelly than her own deadly illness.
Dialogue: 2,0:16:50.25,0:16:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Mummy dying with it
Dialogue: 2,0:16:52.64,0:16:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Christ dying with it
Dialogue: 2,0:16:55.48,0:16:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}nailed hand and foot.
Dialogue: 2,0:16:59.38,0:17:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}High among the crowds and the soldiers.
Dialogue: 2,0:17:03.45,0:17:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}No comfort except a sponge of vinegar
Dialogue: 2,0:17:06.43,0:17:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and the kind words of a thief
Dialogue: 2,0:17:11.75,0:17:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}hanging forever
Dialogue: 2,0:17:16.19,0:17:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}over the bed in the night nursery.
Dialogue: 2,0:17:27.56,0:17:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}There's no way back.
Dialogue: 2,0:17:33.11,0:17:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}The gate's barred.
Dialogue: 2,0:17:36.09,0:17:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}All the saints and angels posted along the wall.
Dialogue: 2,0:17:41.42,0:17:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Thrown away, scrapped, rotting down.
Dialogue: 2,0:17:49.46,0:17:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Nameless and dead.
Dialogue: 2,0:17:55.92,0:17:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Like the baby they wrapped up
Dialogue: 2,0:17:58.79,0:18:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and took away before I had a chance to see her.
Dialogue: 2,0:18:46.05,0:18:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Well, Bridey is one for bombshells, isn't he?
Dialogue: 2,0:19:17.03,0:19:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Considering that I've just recovered from a fit of hysteria
Dialogue: 2,0:19:20.01,0:19:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I don't call that at all bad.
Dialogue: 2,0:19:24.04,0:19:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Most hysterical women look as if they've got a bad cold.
Dialogue: 2,0:19:28.86,0:19:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Come on.
Dialogue: 2,0:19:30.50,0:19:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}We're not going down again?
Dialogue: 2,0:19:32.38,0:19:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Of course.
Dialogue: 2,0:19:33.67,0:19:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}We can't leave Bridey alone on his engagement night.
Dialogue: 2,0:19:36.87,0:19:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Can't we?
Dialogue: 2,0:19:41.58,0:19:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I'm sorry about that appalling scene, Charles.
Dialogue: 2,0:19:44.95,0:19:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I can't explain it.
Dialogue: 2,0:19:58.66,0:20:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Was it nice out?
Dialogue: 2,0:20:00.18,0:20:02.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}If I'd known you were going I'd have come too.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:03.84,0:20:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Rather cold.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:07.74,0:20:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I hope it's not going to be inconvenient for Rex
Dialogue: 2,0:20:10.51,0:20:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}moving out of here.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:12.10,0:20:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You see, Barton Street is much too small for us
Dialogue: 2,0:20:13.90,0:20:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and the three children.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:15.50,0:20:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Besides, Beryl likes the country.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:18.45,0:20:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}In his letter
Dialogue: 2,0:20:19.23,0:20:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Papa proposed making over the whole estate right away.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:23.50,0:20:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I'm sure he'll be sorry to leave.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:27.58,0:20:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Oh, don't worry. Rex'll find another bargain somewhere.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:31.94,0:20:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Trust him.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:35.02,0:20:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Beryl has some furniture of her own she's very attached to.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:38.18,0:20:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I don't think it would go very well here.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:40.49,0:20:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You know, oak dressers and coffin stools and things.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:43.59,0:20:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I thought you could put it in Mother's room.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:45.63,0:20:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Yes, that would be the place for it
Dialogue: 2,0:20:48.03,0:20:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}of course nobody has used that room for years.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:49.61,0:20:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}So brother and sister sat and talked
Dialogue: 2,0:20:51.56,0:20:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}about the arrangement of the house until bed-time.
Dialogue: 2,0:20:55.26,0:20:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}An hour ago, I thought
Dialogue: 2,0:20:56.71,0:21:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}by the fountain, she wept her heart out
Dialogue: 2,0:21:00.70,0:21:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}for the death of her God.
Dialogue: 2,0:21:02.66,0:21:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Now she is discussing whether Beryl's children
Dialogue: 2,0:21:05.26,0:21:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Shall take the old smoking room
Dialogue: 2,0:21:07.22,0:21:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}or the school room for their own.
Dialogue: 2,0:21:10.10,0:21:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I was all at sea.
Dialogue: 2,0:21:16.66,0:21:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I won't believe that great spout of tears came just
Dialogue: 2,0:21:18.98,0:21:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}from a few words of Bridey's.
Dialogue: 2,0:21:22.14,0:21:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You must have been thinking about it before.
Dialogue: 2,0:21:24.54,0:21:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Hardly at all.
Dialogue: 2,0:21:27.42,0:21:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Now and then.
Dialogue: 2,0:21:30.54,0:21:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}more, lately with the Last Trump so near.
Dialogue: 2,0:21:35.06,0:21:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Of course, it's a thing psychologists could explain.
Dialogue: 2,0:21:41.70,0:21:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}A pre-conditioning from childhood
Dialogue: 2,0:21:43.62,0:21:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}feelings of guilt from the nonsense you were taught in the nursery.
Dialogue: 2,0:21:57.18,0:21:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You do know in your heart
Dialogue: 2,0:21:59.58,0:22:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}that it's all bosh, don't you?
Dialogue: 2,0:22:04.98,0:22:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}How I wish it was.
Dialogue: 2,0:22:09.14,0:22:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Do you know, Sebastian once said almost the same thing to me.
Dialogue: 2,0:22:15.10,0:22:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He's gone back to the Church, you know.
Dialogue: 2,0:22:20.10,0:22:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Of course, he's never left it as definitely as I did.
Dialogue: 2,0:22:25.14,0:22:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I've gone too far.
Dialogue: 2,0:22:28.14,0:22:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}There's no turning back.
Dialogue: 2,0:22:31.26,0:22:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I know that, if that's what you mean by thinking it all bosh.
Dialogue: 2,0:22:40.74,0:22:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Let's go out again.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:19.42,0:23:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It's like the setting for a comedy.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:21.54,0:23:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Scene: A baroque fountain in a noblemans grounds.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:28.74,0:23:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Act one, sunset.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:31.74,0:23:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Act two, moonlight.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:35.14,0:23:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Act three, towards dawn.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:37.70,0:23:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}The characters keep assembling at the fountain for no very clear reason.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:42.62,0:23:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Comedy.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:44.33,0:23:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Drama
Dialogue: 2,0:23:45.62,0:23:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}tragedy, farce
Dialogue: 2,0:23:49.10,0:23:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}What you will.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:54.14,0:23:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}This is the reconciliation scene.
Dialogue: 2,0:23:59.42,0:24:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Was there a quarrel?
Dialogue: 2,0:24:02.10,0:24:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Misunderstanding and estrangement in Act Two.
Dialogue: 2,0:24:06.26,0:24:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Don't talk in that damned bounderish way.
Dialogue: 2,0:24:09.06,0:24:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Why must you see everything second hand?
Dialogue: 2,0:24:12.14,0:24:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Why must this be a play?
Dialogue: 2,0:24:18.02,0:24:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It's a way I have.
Dialogue: 2,0:24:20.02,0:24:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I hate it.
Dialogue: 2,0:24:27.34,0:24:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Now do you see how I hate it?
Dialogue: 2,0:24:33.38,0:24:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Did that hurt?
Dialogue: 2,0:24:35.26,0:24:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Yes.
Dialogue: 2,0:24:37.54,0:24:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Did it?
Dialogue: 2,0:24:40.10,0:24:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Did I?
Dialogue: 2,0:24:44.42,0:24:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Cat on the rooftop.
Dialogue: 2,0:24:47.74,0:24:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Beast!
Dialogue: 2,0:24:58.82,0:25:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Cat in the moonlight.
Dialogue: 2,0:25:20.78,0:25:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Your poor face.
Dialogue: 2,0:25:25.98,0:25:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Will there be a mark tomorrow?
Dialogue: 2,0:25:28.26,0:25:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I expect so.
Dialogue: 2,0:25:35.14,0:25:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Charles, am I going crazy?
Dialogue: 2,0:25:41.02,0:25:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}What's happened here tonight?
Dialogue: 2,0:25:51.02,0:25:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I'm so tired.
Dialogue: 2,0:25:58.10,0:26:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}So tired
Dialogue: 2,0:26:02.22,0:26:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Tired and crazy and good for nothing.
Dialogue: 2,0:26:09.10,0:26:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}All I can hope to do is put my life in some sort of order.
Dialogue: 2,0:26:13.98,0:26:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}That's why I want to marry you.
Dialogue: 2,0:26:18.54,0:26:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I should like to have a child.
Dialogue: 2,0:26:24.50,0:26:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}That's one thing I can do
Dialogue: 2,0:26:45.18,0:26:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}So you're being divorced.
Dialogue: 2,0:26:46.98,0:26:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Isn't that rather unnecessary after being happy together
Dialogue: 2,0:26:49.95,0:26:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}all these years?
Dialogue: 2,0:26:52.94,0:26:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}We weren't particularly happy, you know.
Dialogue: 2,0:26:54.96,0:26:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Weren't you?
Dialogue: 2,0:26:56.42,0:26:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Were you not?
Dialogue: 2,0:26:58.34,0:27:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I distinctly remember last Christmas seeing you together and thinking
Dialogue: 2,0:27:02.15,0:27:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}how happy you looked, and wondering why.
Dialogue: 2,0:27:05.74,0:27:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You'll find it very disturbing, you know, starting off again.
Dialogue: 2,0:27:08.03,0:27:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}How old are you, thirty four?
Dialogue: 2,0:27:09.48,0:27:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}That's no time to be starting. You ought to be settling down.
Dialogue: 2,0:27:13.82,0:27:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Have you made any plans?
Dialogue: 2,0:27:15.66,0:27:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Yes.
Dialogue: 2,0:27:17.18,0:27:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I intend to get married again as soon as the divorce is through.
Dialogue: 2,0:27:20.50,0:27:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Well, I do call that a lot of nonsense.
Dialogue: 2,0:27:24.18,0:27:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I can understand a man wishing he hadn't married
Dialogue: 2,0:27:26.03,0:27:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}And trying to get out of it
Dialogue: 2,0:27:27.06,0:27:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Though I never felt anything of the kind myself
Dialogue: 2,0:27:30.03,0:27:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}But to get rid of one wife and take up another immediately
Dialogue: 2,0:27:33.05,0:27:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}is beyond all reason.
Dialogue: 2,0:27:36.46,0:27:38.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I've seen quite a few divorces in my time.
Dialogue: 2,0:27:38.78,0:27:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I've never known one work out so happily
Dialogue: 2,0:27:40.65,0:27:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}for all concerned.
Dialogue: 2,0:27:43.30,0:27:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Almost always
Dialogue: 2,0:27:44.19,0:27:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}However matey people are at the start
Dialogue: 2,0:27:48.04,0:27:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}bad blood crops up as soon as they get down to detail.
Dialogue: 2,0:27:53.26,0:27:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Mind you, I don't mind saying that there have been times
Dialogue: 2,0:27:56.62,0:27:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}In the last couple of years when I thought
Dialogue: 2,0:27:57.90,0:27:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}you were a bit rough on Celia.
Dialogue: 2,0:28:07.26,0:28:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Course it's different when it's one's own sister.
Dialogue: 2,0:28:11.78,0:28:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I've always thought her a jolly attractive girl.
Dialogue: 2,0:28:15.98,0:28:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}The sort of girl any chap would be glad to have
Dialogue: 2,0:28:18.82,0:28:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}artistic too
Dialogue: 2,0:28:20.78,0:28:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}just down your street.
Dialogue: 2,0:28:29.26,0:28:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I must admit.
Dialogue: 2,0:28:30.86,0:28:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You're a good picker.
Dialogue: 2,0:28:35.06,0:28:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I've always had a soft spot for Julia.
Dialogue: 2,0:28:39.18,0:28:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Well, I suppose if Julia insists on a divorce
Dialogue: 2,0:28:42.73,0:28:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}she must have one.
Dialogue: 2,0:28:47.02,0:28:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}My God, she couldn't have chosen a worse time.
Dialogue: 2,0:28:49.89,0:28:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Things had not gone as smoothly for Rex
Dialogue: 2,0:28:52.14,0:28:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}as he had planned.
Dialogue: 2,0:28:53.82,0:28:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Only war could put his fortunes right
Dialogue: 2,0:28:56.14,0:28:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and carry him into power.
Dialogue: 2,0:28:58.54,0:29:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}A divorce would do him no great harm
Dialogue: 2,0:29:01.62,0:29:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}but he was like a gambler with a big bank running
Dialogue: 2,0:29:05.10,0:29:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He could not look up from the table.
Dialogue: 2,0:29:07.62,0:29:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Tell her to
Dialogue: 2,0:29:10.02,0:29:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}tell her to hang on a bit, Charles, there's a good fellow.
Dialogue: 2,0:29:26.18,0:29:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I met the widow at luncheon.
Dialogue: 2,0:29:30.14,0:29:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Did you?
Dialogue: 2,0:29:32.30,0:29:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Do you know what she said to me?
Dialogue: 2,0:29:35.02,0:29:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}So you're divorcing one divorced man
Dialogue: 2,0:29:38.78,0:29:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and marrying another. It sounds rather complicated
Dialogue: 2,0:29:42.24,0:29:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}but my dear, she called me my dear about twenty times
Dialogue: 2,0:29:45.70,0:29:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I've usually found that every Catholic family
Dialogue: 2,0:29:48.40,0:29:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}has one lapsed member, and it's often the nicest.
Dialogue: 2,0:29:53.98,0:29:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}What's she like?
Dialogue: 2,0:29:55.34,0:29:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Majestic.
Dialogue: 2,0:29:57.10,0:29:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}And voluptuous.
Dialogue: 2,0:29:58.42,0:29:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Common, of course.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:00.38,0:30:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I'll tell you one thing. She's lied to Bridey
Dialogue: 2,0:30:02.43,0:30:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}about her age. She's a good forty five.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:05.10,0:30:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I don't see her providing an heir.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:08.50,0:30:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Bridey can't take his eyes off her.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:10.26,0:30:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He was gloating on her in the most revolting way all through luncheon.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:14.54,0:30:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Was she friendly?
Dialogue: 2,0:30:15.82,0:30:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Goodness, yes
Dialogue: 2,0:30:17.64,0:30:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}In a condescending way.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:20.29,0:30:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I think it put her rather at ease to have me there as the black sheep.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:24.50,0:30:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}She concentrated on me in fact, said rather pointedly
Dialogue: 2,0:30:27.50,0:30:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}she hoped to see me often in London.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:30.42,0:30:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I think Bridey's scruples only extend to her sleeping
Dialogue: 2,0:30:32.98,0:30:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}under the same roof with me. Apparently I can do her
Dialogue: 2,0:30:35.42,0:30:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}no serious harm in a hat shop or hairdresser's.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:40.34,0:30:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}The scruples are all on Bridey's part, anyway.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:42.42,0:30:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}The widow is madly tough.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:44.18,0:30:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Does she boss him?
Dialogue: 2,0:30:45.34,0:30:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Not yet, much.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:47.18,0:30:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He's in an amorous stupor, poor beast and doesn't know where he is.
Dialogue: 2,0:30:52.74,0:30:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}She's just a good-hearted woman who wants a good home
Dialogue: 2,0:30:56.14,0:30:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}for her children and isn't going to let anything stand in her way.
Dialogue: 2,0:31:04.66,0:31:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}A telephone message, my Lady, from Lady Cordelia.
Dialogue: 2,0:31:07.46,0:31:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Lady Cordelia? How marvelous.
Dialogue: 2,0:31:11.58,0:31:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(160,160)}Where is she?
Dialogue: 2,0:31:11.94,0:31:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}In London, my Lady.
Dialogue: 2,0:31:13.45,0:31:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Wilcox, how lovely.
Dialogue: 2,0:31:15.18,0:31:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Is she coming home?
Dialogue: 2,0:31:16.73,0:31:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Just starting for the station. She'll be here after dinner.
Dialogue: 2,0:31:19.47,0:31:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Thank you.
Dialogue: 2,0:31:25.26,0:31:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I haven't seen her since I took her to dinner at the Ritz
Dialogue: 2,0:31:28.66,0:31:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and she talked about becoming a nun.
Dialogue: 2,0:31:31.30,0:31:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It must be twelve years!
Dialogue: 2,0:31:35.74,0:31:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}She was an enchanting child.
Dialogue: 2,0:31:38.90,0:31:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}She's had an odd life.
Dialogue: 2,0:31:40.78,0:31:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}First the convent
Dialogue: 2,0:31:42.18,0:31:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and when that was no good, the war in Spain.
Dialogue: 2,0:31:44.70,0:31:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Then staying on when the war was over and helping in the camps.
Dialogue: 2,0:31:58.54,0:32:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}She's grown up quite plain, you know.
Dialogue: 2,0:32:03.02,0:32:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Does she know about us?
Dialogue: 2,0:32:04.74,0:32:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Yes.
Dialogue: 2,0:32:06.38,0:32:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}She wrote me a sweet letter.
Dialogue: 2,0:32:37.42,0:32:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It hurt to think of Cordelia
Dialogue: 2,0:32:39.76,0:32:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}growing up quite plain.
Dialogue: 2,0:32:41.94,0:32:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}To think at all that.
Dialogue: 2,0:32:43.58,0:32:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Burning love
Dialogue: 2,0:32:45.26,0:32:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}spending itself on serum injections
Dialogue: 2,0:32:46.98,0:32:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and delousing powder.
Dialogue: 2,0:32:49.26,0:32:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}When she arrived
Dialogue: 2,0:32:50.67,0:32:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}tired from her journey
Dialogue: 2,0:32:51.79,0:32:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}rather shabby
Dialogue: 2,0:32:53.26,0:32:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}moving in the manner of one who has no interest in pleasing
Dialogue: 2,0:32:57.02,0:32:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I thought her an ugly woman.
Dialogue: 2,0:33:00.18,0:33:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It was odd, I thought
Dialogue: 2,0:33:01.72,0:33:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}how the same ingredients, differently dispersed
Dialogue: 2,0:33:04.07,0:33:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}could produce Brideshead, Sebastian, Julia and her.
Dialogue: 2,0:33:12.70,0:33:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It's wonderful to be home.
Dialogue: 2,0:33:16.78,0:33:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}My job's over in Spain.
Dialogue: 2,0:33:20.10,0:33:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}The authorities were very polite
Dialogue: 2,0:33:22.46,0:33:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}thanked me for all I'd done
Dialogue: 2,0:33:24.50,0:33:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}gave me a medal
Dialogue: 2,0:33:27.54,0:33:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and sent me packing.
Dialogue: 2,0:33:32.10,0:33:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Mind you, it looks as though there'll be plenty
Dialogue: 2,0:33:34.48,0:33:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}of the same sort of work over here soon.
Dialogue: 2,0:33:38.14,0:33:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Rex seems pretty certain.
Dialogue: 2,0:33:40.54,0:33:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He's made up his mind there's going to be a war.
Dialogue: 2,0:33:45.10,0:33:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I wonder what Papa will do?
Dialogue: 2,0:33:50.58,0:33:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Where is Rex? Is he coming down?
Dialogue: 2,0:33:53.82,0:33:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}No. The lawyers insisted on a formal separation
Dialogue: 2,0:33:56.77,0:33:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}so he's moved back to London. I'm only staying until
Dialogue: 2,0:33:59.55,0:34:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Bridey is installed with the widow and her children.
Dialogue: 2,0:34:03.38,0:34:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He wrote to me and said if I was homeless
Dialogue: 2,0:34:06.96,0:34:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I could stay here after they've moved in.
Dialogue: 2,0:34:10.94,0:34:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I don't know though
Dialogue: 2,0:34:13.26,0:34:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Mrs. Muspratt and the three boys.
Dialogue: 2,0:34:19.18,0:34:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Maybe I'll get myself a flat in London.
Dialogue: 2,0:34:34.10,0:34:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Hello Nanny.
Dialogue: 2,0:34:41.18,0:34:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I knew you'd be up.
Dialogue: 2,0:34:43.54,0:34:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Mr. Wilcox sent to tell me you were coming.
Dialogue: 2,0:34:50.02,0:34:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I brought you some lace.
Dialogue: 2,0:34:56.10,0:34:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}That is nice, dear.
Dialogue: 2,0:34:59.14,0:35:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Just like her poor Ladyship used to wear at Mass.
Dialogue: 2,0:35:02.32,0:35:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Though why they made it black? I never did understand
Dialogue: 2,0:35:06.18,0:35:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}seeing lace is white naturally.
Dialogue: 2,0:35:09.26,0:35:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Well, that'll be very welcome I'm sure.
Dialogue: 2,0:35:18.66,0:35:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}May we turn the wireless off Nanny?
Dialogue: 2,0:35:21.10,0:35:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Why of course. I didn't notice it was on
Dialogue: 2,0:35:24.98,0:35:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}in the pleasure of seeing you.
Dialogue: 2,0:35:28.06,0:35:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Isn't it splendid about Julia and Charles getting married?
Dialogue: 2,0:35:36.18,0:35:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Well I hope it's all for the best.
Dialogue: 2,0:35:39.14,0:35:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Brideshead has certainly taken long enough to make up his mind.
Dialogue: 2,0:35:43.16,0:35:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I've hunted all through Debrett and I couldn't find any mention
Dialogue: 2,0:35:47.86,0:35:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}of Mrs. Muspratt's connections.
Dialogue: 2,0:35:50.62,0:35:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}She caught him, I daresay.
Dialogue: 2,0:35:55.34,0:35:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}What have you done to your hair?
Dialogue: 2,0:35:57.30,0:35:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Oh I know, it's terrible.
Dialogue: 2,0:35:59.82,0:36:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I must get all that put right now I'm back.
Dialogue: 2,0:36:03.34,0:36:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Darling nanny.
Dialogue: 2,0:36:06.46,0:36:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I saw Sebastian last month.
Dialogue: 2,0:36:08.86,0:36:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}What a time he's been gone. Was he quite well?
Dialogue: 2,0:36:12.06,0:36:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Not very. That's why I went.
Dialogue: 2,0:36:14.29,0:36:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It's quite near you know, from Spain to Tunis.
Dialogue: 2,0:36:17.42,0:36:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He's with the monks there.
Dialogue: 2,0:36:19.42,0:36:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Oh, well I hope they look after him properly.
Dialogue: 2,0:36:21.87,0:36:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I expect they find him a regular handful.
Dialogue: 2,0:36:25.66,0:36:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He always sends to me at Christmas.
Dialogue: 2,0:36:28.50,0:36:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Though it's not the same as having him home.
Dialogue: 2,0:36:33.06,0:36:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He's got a beard now and he's very religious.
Dialogue: 2,0:36:36.54,0:36:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}That I won't believe, not even if I see it.
Dialogue: 2,0:36:40.02,0:36:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He was always a little heathen.
Dialogue: 2,0:36:41.94,0:36:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Brideshead was one for Church, not Sebastian.
Dialogue: 2,0:36:46.26,0:36:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}And a beard!
Dialogue: 2,0:36:48.30,0:36:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Only fancy
Dialogue: 2,0:36:50.26,0:36:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Such a nice, fair skin as he had
Dialogue: 2,0:36:52.92,0:36:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Always looked clean, though he'd not been
Dialogue: 2,0:36:55.24,0:36:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}near water all day.
Dialogue: 2,0:36:56.78,0:37:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}While Brideshead there was no doing anything with.
Dialogue: 2,0:37:11.18,0:37:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Cordelia!
Dialogue: 2,0:37:13.10,0:37:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}What?
Dialogue: 2,0:37:15.58,0:37:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Come and tell me about Sebastian.
Dialogue: 2,0:37:17.64,0:37:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Not now, Charles.
Dialogue: 2,0:37:19.23,0:37:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It's a long story. Tomorrow.
Dialogue: 2,0:37:22.14,0:37:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Goodnight.
Dialogue: 2,0:37:25.06,0:37:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Goodnight.
Dialogue: 2,0:37:30.14,0:37:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I had not forgotten Sebastian.
Dialogue: 2,0:37:33.10,0:37:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He was with me daily in Julia
Dialogue: 2,0:37:36.10,0:37:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}or perhaps it was Julia I had known in him
Dialogue: 2,0:37:39.17,0:37:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}in those distant Arcadian days.
Dialogue: 2,0:37:42.18,0:37:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Every stone of the house had a memory of him
Dialogue: 2,0:37:46.22,0:37:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}And hearing him spoken of by Cordelia
Dialogue: 2,0:37:49.02,0:37:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}As someone she had seen a month ago
Dialogue: 2,0:37:52.02,0:37:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}my lost friend filled my thoughts.
Dialogue: 2,0:37:57.18,0:37:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I heard he was dying.
Dialogue: 2,0:37:59.98,0:38:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}A journalist in Burgos told me
Dialogue: 2,0:38:02.85,0:38:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}who'd just arrived from North Africa.
Dialogue: 2,0:38:06.30,0:38:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}A down and out called Flyte
Dialogue: 2,0:38:10.14,0:38:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}who people said was an English Lord
Dialogue: 2,0:38:13.14,0:38:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Has been found starving
Dialogue: 2,0:38:15.15,0:38:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}And taken in to a monastery
Dialogue: 2,0:38:16.64,0:38:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}near Carthage.
Dialogue: 2,0:38:18.30,0:38:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}That was how the story reached me.
Dialogue: 2,0:38:20.94,0:38:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I knew it couldn't quite be true
Dialogue: 2,0:38:23.46,0:38:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}however little we did for Sebastian
Dialogue: 2,0:38:25.72,0:38:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}he at least got his money sent to him.
Dialogue: 2,0:38:28.82,0:38:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}But I started off at once.
Dialogue: 2,0:38:33.18,0:38:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It was quite easy to find him.
Dialogue: 2,0:38:36.14,0:38:38.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I just went to the consulate.
Dialogue: 2,0:38:39.22,0:38:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Apparently he'd turned up in Tunis one day
Dialogue: 2,0:38:42.45,0:38:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and applied to be taken on as a missionary lay brother.
Dialogue: 2,0:38:47.90,0:38:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}The fathers took one look at him and turned him down.
Dialogue: 2,0:38:52.50,0:38:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Then he started drinking again.
Dialogue: 2,0:38:58.70,0:39:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He lived in a little hotel on the edge of the Arab Quarter.
Dialogue: 2,0:39:03.54,0:39:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I went to see the place later.
Dialogue: 2,0:39:06.94,0:39:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It was a bar with a few rooms over it
Dialogue: 2,0:39:09.86,0:39:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Smelling of hot oil and garlic and stale wine.
Dialogue: 2,0:39:15.50,0:39:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He stayed there a month drinking Greek absinthe.
Dialogue: 2,0:39:23.06,0:39:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}They loved him there.
Dialogue: 2,0:39:26.22,0:39:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He's still loved you see.
Dialogue: 2,0:39:28.54,0:39:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Whatever he does, whatever condition he's in.
Dialogue: 2,0:39:34.78,0:39:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It's a thing about him he'll never lose.
Dialogue: 2,0:39:41.18,0:39:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}They thought very ill of his family for leaving him like that.
Dialogue: 2,0:39:45.90,0:39:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It wouldn't happen with their people, they said.
Dialogue: 2,0:39:50.18,0:39:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}And I daresay they're right.
Dialogue: 2,0:39:54.22,0:39:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Anyway, that was later.
Dialogue: 2,0:39:56.98,0:39:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}After the consulate
Dialogue: 2,0:39:58.30,0:40:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I went straight to the monastery and I saw the Superior.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:01.18,0:40:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He told me his part of the story.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:06.86,0:40:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}So I sent him away.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:09.18,0:40:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He kept coming back
Dialogue: 2,0:40:10.97,0:40:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}two or three times a week
Dialogue: 2,0:40:13.62,0:40:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}always drunk
Dialogue: 2,0:40:15.66,0:40:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}until I gave orders to the porter to keep him out.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:20.70,0:40:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He must have been a terrible nuisance to you.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:23.38,0:40:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I don't know what I can do to help him
Dialogue: 2,0:40:25.79,0:40:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}except pray.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:28.22,0:40:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Finally, we found him unconscious outside the main gate
Dialogue: 2,0:40:33.10,0:40:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}he had fallen down and had lain there all night.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:37.86,0:40:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}At first we thought that he was merely drunk again
Dialogue: 2,0:40:40.71,0:40:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}then we realised that he was very ill
Dialogue: 2,0:40:43.50,0:40:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}so we took him to the Infirmary.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:46.26,0:40:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He's been there ever since.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:51.74,0:40:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}They'd given him a room to himself
Dialogue: 2,0:40:53.66,0:40:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}just off the cloisters.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:57.22,0:40:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He looked terrible.
Dialogue: 2,0:40:59.34,0:41:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Any age.
Dialogue: 2,0:41:01.90,0:41:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}At first he couldn't talk much
Dialogue: 2,0:41:04.22,0:41:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}But I stayed a fortnight with him
Dialogue: 2,0:41:06.20,0:41:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}until he was over the worst of his illness.
Dialogue: 2,0:41:08.22,0:41:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Then he told me what had been happening to him.
Dialogue: 2,0:41:12.18,0:41:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It was mostly about Kurt, his German friend.
Dialogue: 2,0:41:17.18,0:41:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Well you've met him, so you know all about that.
Dialogue: 2,0:41:20.70,0:41:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Sounds gruesome.
Dialogue: 2,0:41:23.98,0:41:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He said they went to Greece
Dialogue: 2,0:41:26.22,0:41:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}And Kurt had got arrested after some brawl
Dialogue: 2,0:41:29.24,0:41:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and sent back to Germany.
Dialogue: 2,0:41:31.30,0:41:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It was a time when they were rounding up all their nationals
Dialogue: 2,0:41:34.51,0:41:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}from all parts of the world, to make them into Nazis.
Dialogue: 2,0:41:40.26,0:41:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Sebastian followed.
Dialogue: 2,0:41:53.82,0:41:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}For a year he couldn't find any trace of him.
Dialogue: 2,0:41:57.82,0:42:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Then in the end he ran him to earth dressed as a storm trooper
Dialogue: 2,0:42:01.26,0:42:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}in a provincial town.
Dialogue: 2,0:42:05.02,0:42:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}At first he wouldn't have anything to do with Sebastian
Dialogue: 2,0:42:10.02,0:42:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}spouting all that official jargon about the rebirth of his country.
Dialogue: 2,0:42:15.42,0:42:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}But it was only skin deep with him.
Dialogue: 2,0:42:21.02,0:42:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Six years of Sebastian had taught him more
Dialogue: 2,0:42:24.77,0:42:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}than a year of Hitler.
Dialogue: 2,0:42:28.65,0:42:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Eventually Kurt chucked it and admitted he hated Germany
Dialogue: 2,0:42:31.53,0:42:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and wanted to get out.
Dialogue: 2,0:42:35.09,0:42:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I don't know how much it was simple the call of the easy life
Dialogue: 2,0:42:38.50,0:42:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}sponging on Sebastian.
Dialogue: 2,0:42:41.45,0:42:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He said it wasn't entirely that
Dialogue: 2,0:42:45.33,0:42:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}but Kurt had just begun to grow up.
Dialogue: 2,0:42:50.09,0:42:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Maybe he's right.
Dialogue: 2,0:42:54.01,0:42:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Anyway, it didn't work.
Dialogue: 2,0:42:56.81,0:43:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Kurt always got into trouble whatever he did.
Dialogue: 2,0:43:00.41,0:43:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Finally they caught him and they put him in a concentration camp.
Dialogue: 2,0:43:06.25,0:43:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Sebastian couldn't get near him.
Dialogue: 2,0:43:11.09,0:43:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He didn't even know what camp he was in.
Dialogue: 2,0:43:16.09,0:43:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}So he hung about in Germany for another year
Dialogue: 2,0:43:19.81,0:43:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Drinking again.
Dialogue: 2,0:43:24.65,0:43:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Until one day in his cups
Dialogue: 2,0:43:28.70,0:43:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He took up with a man who'd just been out of the camp
Dialogue: 2,0:43:31.18,0:43:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Where Kurt had been
Dialogue: 2,0:43:35.15,0:43:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}And learned that he had hanged himself in his hut
Dialogue: 2,0:43:38.63,0:43:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}in the first week.
Dialogue: 2,0:43:45.13,0:43:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}So that was the end of Europe for Sebastian.
Dialogue: 2,0:43:55.69,0:43:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He went back to North Africa
Dialogue: 2,0:43:59.09,0:44:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}where he had been happy.
Dialogue: 2,0:44:51.72,0:44:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I once had a governess who jumped off this bridge and drowned herself.
Dialogue: 2,0:44:57.40,0:44:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I know.
Dialogue: 2,0:44:59.68,0:45:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}How could you know?
Dialogue: 2,0:45:02.08,0:45:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It was the first thing I ever heard about you
Dialogue: 2,0:45:04.48,0:45:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}before I ever met you.
Dialogue: 2,0:45:07.20,0:45:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}How very odd.
Dialogue: 2,0:45:26.24,0:45:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Have you told Julia this about Sebastian?
Dialogue: 2,0:45:30.48,0:45:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}The substance of it.
Dialogue: 2,0:45:33.68,0:45:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Not quite as I told you.
Dialogue: 2,0:45:38.04,0:45:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}She never really loved him
Dialogue: 2,0:45:40.80,0:45:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You know, as we do.
Dialogue: 2,0:45:50.04,0:45:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Poor old Sebastian.
Dialogue: 2,0:45:52.60,0:45:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It's quite pitiful.
Dialogue: 2,0:45:55.96,0:45:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}How will it end?
Dialogue: 2,0:45:58.68,0:46:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I think I can tell you exactly, Charles.
Dialogue: 2,0:46:02.32,0:46:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I've seen others like him.
Dialogue: 2,0:46:04.64,0:46:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}And I believe they are very near and dear to God.
Dialogue: 2,0:46:10.04,0:46:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}They'll let him stay there
Dialogue: 2,0:46:12.24,0:46:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}living half in and half out of the community.
Dialogue: 2,0:46:16.68,0:46:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He'll be a great favorite with the old fathers
Dialogue: 2,0:46:19.60,0:46:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and something of a joke with the novices.
Dialogue: 2,0:46:24.48,0:46:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}There's usually a few odd hangers on in a religious house.
Dialogue: 2,0:46:29.04,0:46:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You know
Dialogue: 2,0:46:31.64,0:46:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}People who don't quite fit in to either the world
Dialogue: 2,0:46:34.37,0:46:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}or the monastic rule.
Dialogue: 2,0:46:37.16,0:46:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I suppose I'm something of that sort myself
Dialogue: 2,0:46:40.88,0:46:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}but as I don't happen to drink I'm more employable.
Dialogue: 2,0:46:47.60,0:46:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He'll disappear for two or three days every month
Dialogue: 2,0:46:51.03,0:46:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Or so and they'll all nod and smile and say
Dialogue: 2,0:46:55.64,0:46:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Old Sebastian on a spree again.
Dialogue: 2,0:47:01.12,0:47:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Then one day, after one of his drinking bouts
Dialogue: 2,0:47:04.88,0:47:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}he'll be picked up at the gate dying
Dialogue: 2,0:47:08.52,0:47:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and show by the mere flicker of his eyelids
Dialogue: 2,0:47:12.04,0:47:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}that he is conscious when they give him the last sacraments.
Dialogue: 2,0:47:19.80,0:47:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Not such a bad way of getting through one's life.
Dialogue: 2,0:47:23.76,0:47:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It's not what one would have foretold.
Dialogue: 2,0:47:31.68,0:47:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}I suppose he doesn't suffer?
Dialogue: 2,0:47:36.76,0:47:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Oh yes, I think he does.
Dialogue: 2,0:47:42.20,0:47:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}One has no idea what the suffering may be
Dialogue: 2,0:47:46.68,0:47:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}to be as maimed as he is.
Dialogue: 2,0:47:51.60,0:47:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}No dignity.
Dialogue: 2,0:47:54.85,0:47:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}No power of will.
Dialogue: 2,0:47:59.23,0:48:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}No one is truly holy without suffering.
Dialogue: 2,0:48:05.64,0:48:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Holy?
Dialogue: 2,0:48:07.88,0:48:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Yes.
Dialogue: 2,0:48:12.28,0:48:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}That's what you've got to understand about Sebastian.
Dialogue: 2,0:48:23.28,0:48:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}He's in a very beautiful place, you know
Dialogue: 2,0:48:26.64,0:48:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}White cloisters, a bell tower
Dialogue: 2,0:48:30.52,0:48:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Rows of green vegetables and a monk watering them when the sun is low.
Dialogue: 2,0:48:33.83,0:48:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You knew I wouldn't understand.
Dialogue: 2,0:48:39.84,0:48:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}You and Julia.
Dialogue: 2,0:48:58.08,0:48:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Tell me Charles
Dialogue: 2,0:49:00.12,0:49:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}When you first met me last night
Dialogue: 2,0:49:02.96,0:49:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Did you think, Poor Cordelia, such an engaging child
Dialogue: 2,0:49:07.99,0:49:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}grown into a plain and pious spinster, full of good works?
Dialogue: 2,0:49:13.64,0:49:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Did you think
Dialogue: 2,0:49:16.04,0:49:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}thwarted?
Dialogue: 2,0:49:20.40,0:49:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Yes, I did.
Dialogue: 2,0:49:25.48,0:49:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}But now I'm not so sure.
Dialogue: 2,0:49:28.52,0:49:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}It's funny you know
Dialogue: 2,0:49:29.66,0:49:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}That's exactly the word that I thought for you and Julia
Dialogue: 2,0:49:33.23,0:49:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}when I saw you up in the nursery with Nanny.
Dialogue: 2,0:49:35.72,0:49:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Thwarted passion' I thought.
Dialogue: 2,0:49:38.00,0:49:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}My divorce case
Dialogue: 2,0:49:39.64,0:49:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}or rather my wife's
Dialogue: 2,0:49:42.38,0:49:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}was due to be heard at about the same time as Bridey was married.
Dialogue: 2,0:49:46.19,0:49:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}But he was to have no triumphal return.
Dialogue: 2,0:49:49.55,0:49:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}Lord Marchmain
Dialogue: 2,0:49:51.32,0:49:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}with a taste for the dramatically inopportune
Dialogue: 2,0:49:54.04,0:49:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}declared his intention in view of the international situation
Dialogue: 2,0:49:57.86,0:49:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}of returning to England
Dialogue: 2,0:49:59.72,0:50:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(200,200)}and passing his declining years in his old home.
